    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="530"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d530">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/10067</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-01">1 December,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Hurley is quite right in what
                    he says and advises in this message.<note n="18" xml:id="d530fn18">Mr. Hurley’s
                        telegram No. 2, for the President, received Nov. 30, 1918, <ref
                            target="#pg_642">p. 642</ref>.</note> I am sorry to say that I did not
                    see what <pb facs="0732" n="644" xml:id="pg_644"/> was involved with regard to
                    our shipping in the plan House sent us about the food administration and which
                    we approved. Will you not be kind enough to have a message sent to Hurley this
                    evening (so that he may receive it early to-morrow morning) expressing my
                    agreement with him in this particular and asking him to confer with and explain
                    to Mr. House, saying that this was an aspect of the arrangement which I had not
                    taken in?</p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W[<hi rend="smallcaps">oodrow</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ilson</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
